It is an independent TypeScript implementation written against the Model Context
Protocol TypeScript SDK (@modelcontextprotocol/sdk). It targets publicly
available UK legal data sources (The National Archives Find Case Law,
legislation.gov.uk, the UK Parliament APIs, GOV.UK/HMRC, Companies House, The
Gazette, EUR-Lex/CELLAR, and the EPO Open Patent Services); those sources and
their data are the property of their respective owners and are used under their
own terms.

The OSCOLA citation patterns in src/modules/citations/parsers.ts are compiled
from primary sources — the neutral-citation scheme (Practice Direction (Citation
of Authorities)) and The National Archives' Find Case Law court list for court
codes, and OSCOLA (4th edn) for law-report series abbreviations — which are
factual reference data.

